  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Reduction of and Improved Operational Response to Gender-based Violence Through Camp Management and Site Planning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on efforts initiated in Phase II, IOM will adjust implementation plans in Phase III and develop activities that will strategically consolidate and improve the sustainability of gender-basedviolence (GBV) mainstreaming initiatives, focusing on camp coordination and camp management (CCCM) and shelter components. The objective for this project is to strengthen institutional capacities and practices to enable more coherent and systematic actions aiming at enhancing the protection environment and reducing exposure to GBV risks in displacements situations.</narrative>
  </description>
